commText: Saha and Shubman Gill are at the crease. Saha is on strike. Swapnil Singh will open the attack

Swapnil Singh to Saha, no run, 90.9kph, tad short on off, punched firmly to cover-point where Jacks stops it with a dive
Swapnil Singh to Saha, no run, 95.2kph, quicker through the air on off, Saha defends it from within the crease

Swapnil Singh to Shubman Gill, no run, just a single from the first over. Was fired on middle and Shubman Gill flicks it to mid-wicket where the fielder stops it with a dive to his left. A lovely over by Swapnil Singh..

Yash Dayal to Sai Sudharsan, no run, swings back in sharply, almost a yorker length as Sai Sudharsan squeezes it to backward point

Siraj to Shubman Gill, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Siraj to Shubman Gill, out Caught by Vijaykumar Vyshak!! Both the GT openers are gone early. On a length around off, Shubman Gill stays put and looks to whip it away, ends up getting a leading edge that has been taken by Vyshak at deep point. Siraj on a roll. Has removed both the openers within the powerplay. Shubman Gill c Vijaykumar Vyshak b Siraj 2(7)
Shahrukh Khan, right handed bat, comes to the crease

Siraj to Shahrukh Khan, FOUR, SRK gets off the mark with a boundary. Short of a length around middle, the ball shapes back in sharply as the inside edge misses the stumps and races away to the fine leg fence. Also the first boundary of this match
This is the first time Siraj has taken more than one wicket in powerplay this IPL
Yash Dayal to Sai Sudharsan, 1 run, on a length around middle and leg, nudged to mid-on with soft hands, a quick single taken

Yash Dayal to Shahrukh Khan, 2 runs, curves back in from a fuller length, Shahrukh Khan drives it straight past the bowler as Virat and Faf stop it and get rid of it respectively. Good tag team effort
Yash Dayal to Shahrukh Khan, no run, in the air but safe. Short and quick on off, Shahrukh Khan looks to pull it away, gets a top edge tha t drops in front of mid-off
Yash Dayal to Shahrukh Khan, 1 run, back of a length around middle and leg, Shahrukh Khan clips it through the on-side for a single
Yash Dayal to Sai Sudharsan, no run, hits the deck on a shorter length, the ball nips away as Sai Sudharsan looks to punch it on the rise, gets beaten due to the away movement
Yash Dayal to Sai Sudharsan, no run, short in length around off, Sai Sudharsan plays it off his back foot, gets an underedge towards the keeper
Cameron Green, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

Green to Shahrukh Khan, 1 run, short in length on off, Shahrukh Khan plays it off the back foot, steering it to point for one

Green to Sai Sudharsan, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Green to Sai Sudharsan, out Caught by Kohli!! Even the reliable Sudharsan departs within the powerplay. Green goes short and quick on off, Sai Sudharsan goes for a pull with lack of footwork and the top edge has been taken by Kohli at mid-off. RCB on top unlike their position in the points table. Sai Sudharsan c Kohli b Green 6(14)
David Miller, left handed bat, comes to the crease

Green to Miller, no run, 133.2kph, on a length around off, pushed to cover by Miller

Green to Miller, FOUR, Miller opens his account with a boundary. Short and wide outside off, Miller latches on to the width provided and plays a cracking square cut, think the fielder stationed inside the circle got his hands to it, however, it was struck really powerfully

Summary (Overs 1-6) > Siraj gets Saha early > GT struggle to score > Siraj gets another as Gill holes out under pressure > Sudharsan falls trying to up the ante as well > RCB off to a fantastic start in the powerplay
Vijaykumar Vyshak, right-arm medium, comes into the attack
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Shahrukh Khan, FOUR, easy pickings. On a length around middle and leg, Shahrukh Khan glances it away to the fine leg fence

Vijaykumar Vyshak to Shahrukh Khan, no run, on the shorter side, Shahrukh Khan goes for a pull, gets beaten on the top edge

Lowest Powerplay totals in IPL 2024 23/3 - GT vs RCB, Bengaluru* 27/3 - PBKS vs SRH, Mullanpur 28/4 - MI vs LSG, Lucknow 30/4 - GT vs DC, Ahmedabad 31/2 - RR vs DC, Jaipur This is also the I0$. The run rate of 7.54 in powerplay is the lowest among all the teams this season.

Review taken by RCB for a caught behind!

Vijaykumar Vyshak to Miller, wide, nothing on UltraEdge and that's a wide. Was a short ball down the leg-side as Miller got beaten as he tried to glance it away. Was close to his gloves but no contact, confirm the replays. It's a wide ball instead. RCB lose a review
Vijaykumar Vyshak to Miller, 1 run, back of a length outside off, Miller steers it to third man for a single

Vijaykumar Vyshak to Shahrukh Khan, FOUR, outside off, shaping away from the batter who throws his hands at it. The outside edge flies over backward point and also beats the fielder sprinting across from third man

Strategic timeout! A good start by the RCB pacers this has been. Siraj, Dayal and Green - all have hit the right lengths today. It's that shortish length which GT batters have struggled to play against. The Titans don't have much batting left after this partnership, they might need an impact sub with the bat tonight. Let's find out what the upcoming phase has in store for us..

21:20 Local Time, 15:50 GMT, 21:20 IST: Superb bowling performance from Bengaluru! Opting to bowl, Swapnil Singh bowled a tidy opening over but it was the pacers who did the damage. Mohammed Siraj bowled in good rhythm to nip out both the GT openers and Green nipped out the in-form Sai Sudharsan with a short ball. The visitors were reduced to the lowest powerplay total of this season. Shahrukh Khan was joined by Miller and they counterattacked to stitch a fifty partnership. Karn dropped Miller on 23, conceded a six in the following over but he had the last laugh as he induced a mishit from the big-hitter to break the 61-run stand. Shahrukh followed him n the very next over, courtesy suicidal running. Rahul Tewatia struck a few boundaries but RCB exploited the two-paceness of the track. RCB are favourites to win three on the bounce. Join us in a bit to find out if Gujarat can put up a fight with the ball.

Vijaykumar Vyshak: Quite happy as the team has done well. Glad that we could restrict them to 150-odd. Our bowling coach told be to hit the right areas, we executed our plans. We tried hard with the bouncers, happy that I got a couple of wickets. I have been working hard with the fielding coach, that is helping me. Taking one game at a time. It's a bit swollen, my both hands are swollen but I am okay. Pretty sure that we will get that total.
Stats: -> This is the lowest total at Bengaluru this season. -> This is the 3rd time GT have got all-out this season - most by a team -> This is the lowest team total in RCB-GT matches.

Welcome back. The chasing side has won all four I0$ encounters. Bengaluru chased down GT's 200 with four overs to spare a few days ago. How will they go about their business? Let's find out. Mohit Sharma has the new ball in his hand. One slip in place. Off we go...
